Package com.github.moribund.net.packets

Packets that the server and client send and receive for information between the two distance connection stops.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Packet
    The Packet interface is here to enforce that whatever we are sending through the TCP connection in PacketDispatcher is only a Packet and not random data bits.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DrawNewPlayerPacket
    An instruction by the server to the client to draw a new Player onto the screen.
    KeyPressedPacket
    Sends a packet to the server to allow for client-server latency of the Input.Keys value pressed by the Player that owns this client.
    KeyPressedResponsePacket
    The Input.Keys value pressed response back from the server to enact what to do when the key is pressed.
    KeyUnpressedPacket
    Sends a packet to the server to allow for client-server latency of the Input.Keys value released by the Player that owns this client.
    KeyUnpressedResponsePacket
    The Input.Keys value pressed response back from the server to enact what to do when the key is released.
    LoginPacket
    The response from the server that a Player has logged in.
    LoginRequestPacket
    The request sent by the client to the server that a person is making an account, so it must register that request and follow instructions to handle the player server-sided.
    TilePacket
    The TilePacket sends the Tile of a given player to update the server.
